Diagnosis.
Style (
Figs 9–10
) with apical half enlarged, apex slightly emarginate. Aedeagus (
Figs 11–13
) with flap-like process on the left side at mid-lenght with one continuous row of spines bifurcating near the apex.

External morphology.
Crown (
Fig. 2
) with anterior margin rounded produced anterad beyond eyes, slightly wider than long, interocular width about one-third of transocular width; lateral margins slightly divergent; disk slightly depressed. Clypeus (
Fig. 3
) long and broad; lateral margins converging apically; apex convex, slightly larger than base. Clypellus (
Fig. 3
) V-shaped, four-ninths length of clypeus; in lateral view (
Fig. 4
), with basal half swollen Pronotum (
Fig. 2
) large, distinctly larger than head; median length about twice crown median length; surface striate. Scutellum (
Fig. 2
) large, median length about four-ninths of pronotum median length. Forewing (
Fig. 5
) apex acutely angled; with 3 anteapical cells and 5 apical cells.

Male genitalia.
Pygofer, in lateral view (
Fig. 6
) short, taller than long, apex (
Fig. 7
) apparently bilobed apically: dorsal lobe digitate with dorsal margin with small denticles, ventral lobe rectangular with several setae; caudodorsal process short and spatulate, reaching base of caudal margin lobes; caudoventral process absent. Subgenital plate long, narrow, in lateral view (
Fig. 6
), slightly exceeding apex of pygofer; in ventral view (
Fig. 8
), slightly enlarged on second-third of length, tapering apically; with numerous setae on apical fourth; apex acutely rounded. Connective, in dorsal view (
Fig. 9
), Y-shaped; with well-developed dorsal keel, stem very short; arms long and wide. Style (
Fig. 9
) short, approximately twice length of connective, not reaching apex of aedeagus; in lateral view (
Fig. 10
), apodeme and basal portion of apophysis expanded dorsally, rounded, flap-like; apophysis short, with apical half enlarged, apex slightly emarginate. Aedeagus (
Figs 11–13
) asymmetrical, long and tubular; flap-like process on left side at mid-length with one continuous row of spines bifurcating near apex; gonopore at mid-length; apex hooked; dorsal apodeme long, approximately two-thirds length of shaft. Anal tube with abdominal segment X (
Fig. 6
) long, without process.
